#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Get/set/apply the Retroid Pocket Mini V2 stick RGB (HTR3212, 4 zones per
stick). Mirrors controller-type's get/set/apply + /etc/armada/*.conf pattern.

Every setting below (mode, color, per-mode tunables, duotone colors/split) is
independent per stick - the left and right stick can run completely
different modes at once. Commands that touch one stick's settings take a
<l|r> argument (set, set-mode, set-param, set-duotone-color,
set-duotone-orientation). set-screen-link and set-flash-color stay global:
screen_link is a single brightness-coupling toggle, and flash colors are
keyed by button (a physical button isn't "on" one stick or the other).

Modes:
  static            - always the saved color (or color_source's color).
  breathing         - same color, pulsing.
  rainbow           - saved color ignored; hue cycles continuously, all
                       four zones in lockstep.
  wave              - like rainbow, but each of the 4 zones is offset a
                       quarter-turn around the hue wheel from the next, so
                       the spectrum visibly spreads around the ring instead
                       of the whole stick pulsing as one color.
  starlight         - each zone independently sparks to full brightness at
                       random and fades back on its own, instead of every
                       zone following the same deterministic pattern.
  spin              - same color, ONE zone lit at full brightness, the rest
                       at the intensity floor, stepping around the 4 zones.
                       set-chase <l|r> <on|off> switches the lit zone from a
                       hard single dot to a soft trailing one (uses `size`).
  reactive          - saved color ignored; the stick's own deflection drives
                       its brightness (centered/idle=off, full throw=bright)
                       and angle drives hue, applied evenly across all 4
                       zones. Every button press triggers a brief flash (in
                       that button's own configurable color, set-flash-color
                       <button> <RRGGBB>, default white) on every stick
                       currently in reactive mode. set-compass <l|r>
                       <on|off> instead points the lit zone(s) at the
                       stick's actual push direction (uses `size` for how
                       wide the point is), rather than lighting evenly.
  multidot          - three fixed-hue dots (red/green/blue) chase each other
                       around the 4 zones of the stick.
  ambilight         - saved color ignored; the stick tracks the average
                       color of a strip near its own side of the screen
                       (sampled off the DRM framebuffer via ffmpeg's
                       kmsgrab), fading smoothly between samples rather
                       than snapping.
  duotone           - two configurable colors split across the stick's
                       zones (horizontal/vertical/diagonal, set-duotone-
                       orientation <l|r> <orientation>, colors via
                       set-duotone-color <l|r> <a|b> <RRGGBB>). set-seesaw
                       <l|r> <on|off> makes the two zone groups breathe
                       against each other instead of sitting static.

color_source (set-color-source <l|r> <static|battery|random|shimmer>) - what
"the saved color" actually is, for every mode above that has one (everything
except rainbow/wave/reactive/ambilight/multidot/duotone, which generate
their own):
  static  - the color set via `set`/set-flash-color-style RRGGBB hex.
  battery - interpolated from current battery capacity: red at 20% and
            below, yellow at 60%, green at 100%, gradient between those
            anchors, quantized to 5% steps so ordinary capacity-reading
            jitter doesn't visibly flicker the color. While actually
            charging (not just "Full"), a single zone lights solid blue
            and steps around the stick once per second, overlaid on top
            of whatever the battery-color render already put there -
            toggle with set-charging-indicator <l|r> <on|off>.
  random  - ignores the saved color; jumps to a new random hue every few
            seconds and fades smoothly toward it, unlike rainbow/wave's
            fixed, predictable sweep through the spectrum.
  shimmer - the saved color breathes between a pale, cool version of
            itself and a saturated, warm one (hue swings a few degrees
            toward green/cyan at the cool trough and red/orange at the
            warm peak, saturation swings with it).

(Removed: the old dedicated "battery"/"battery-breathing" modes - color_source
now applies to any mode, and the old "alternating" mode, which lost its
reason to exist once each stick's mode became independently configurable:
its whole point was a phase relationship between the two sticks, which
doesn't mean anything if they're not both running it. "chase" also used to
be its own mode - same ring position/speed as spin, just a different
falloff shape - now it's spin's set-chase toggle instead of a separate
entry.)

Per-mode tunables (set-param <l|r> <param> <mode> <value>), persisted per
stick per mode:
  speed     - animation rate multiplier (0.25-3.0). breathing, spin,
              rainbow, wave, multidot, ambilight (how fast the color chases
              each new screen sample; the sample rate itself is fixed),
              duotone (seesaw's breathing rate), starlight (twinkle rate).
  intensity - how dim the "low point" gets (0.0-0.5): the breathing trough,
              spin/multidot's unlit zones, reactive's brightness right past
              its deadzone, duotone's seesaw trough, starlight's base level.
              Higher = less contrast between lit and unlit.
  size      - how wide the lit point is (1-3 zones). spin (when set-chase
              is on), multidot, reactive (when set-compass is on).

`daemon` runs forever (see armada-stick-led.service): idles at IDLE_INTERVAL
when neither stick is in an animated mode, animates at BREATH_INTERVAL
whenever either stick is.

screen_link (set-screen-link on|off) scales the final brightness by the
panel backlight's current/max ratio, independent of mode, so the sticks dim
and brighten along with the screen.
"""
